  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Improve Responsive Image Display in Image Wrappers\n\nFix the responsive-image-wrapper component to display complete images without cropping, maintaining aspect ratio and proper centering within available space.\n\nRequirements:\n- Modify responsive-image-wrapper to contain entire image within bounds without cropping\n- Implement intelligent fitting: scale by width or height depending on which dimension would exceed container first\n- Maintain original image aspect ratio (no stretching or skewing)\n- Center images both horizontally and vertically within their containers\n- Ensure images never overflow container boundaries regardless of original dimensions\n- Apply same fixes to about-image-wrapper on main page (currently showing cropped images)\n- Consider using image display library (object-fit utilities, dedicated image components) for consistent, polished presentation\n- Test with various image aspect ratios: landscape, portrait, square, extreme ratios\n- Verify behavior across different viewport sizes and container dimensions\n- Ensure solution works for both oversized and undersized images\n\nEdge cases to handle:\n- Very wide panoramic images\n- Very tall portrait images\n- Images smaller than container\n- Images with extreme aspect ratios\n- Dynamic container size changes",
